    "body": "close https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/75\r\n\r\n\r\nThis PR skips `invoke_ffi_init_funcs()` when running under `#[cfg(kmiri)]`.\r\n\r\nThat function relies on linker-defined symbols (`__sinit_array` / `__einit_array`) and assembly/link-time behavior, which KMiri does not model yet ( see https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/78 if we want to model it ). Running it under KMiri causes invalid failures unrelated to normal kernel logic.\r\n",
    "created_at": "2026-06-27T12:53:43Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-06-27T12:58:16Z",
    "closed_at": "2026-06-27T12:58:13Z",
